      <title>Re: Omens NDA Lifted</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=115367#M115367</link>
      <description>Hmm, one thing that you guys seem to be forgetting is how exactly slow mitigation works.. I'm not 100% sure about this, but from what i've heard (and experienced as a 65 shammie) slow mitigating mobs subtract a set percent from your slow.. i.e. if a mob mitigates 30%, and we cast balance of nihil or turgur's insects, the mob is slowed 45% (75-30%) .. if a beastlord comes and slowes the mob with his 65% slow, the mob will be slowed 35% (65-30%). Basically, although our slows do not slow as much anymore, they are still more useful than the other slowing classes.. furthermore, I believe this is an attempt to make it so that slows are not absolutely positively needed anymore. (Granted, with a good cleric, slows are not needed now.. their healing potential is ridiculous imho)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Again, i'm not 100% sure of this, but the general concensus between the shamans i've talked to is that this interpretation of how mitigation works is at least reasonably accurate.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hope this helps :D&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Urgonn, 65 Oracle, VZek server</description>
