    <item>
      <title>Re: Omens NDA Lifted</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=115053#M115053</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;My impression was if you're already fed up with EQ, OoW isn't going to do anything to make you happy again. They often say they don't balance classes with expansions and that's certainly the case.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you're happy playing EQ, you'll probably be happy with what Omens has to offer. It doesn't appear to be the same enormous dissipointment that Gates was, nor are the zones all bland brown and white with the same 4 mobs repeated everywhere you look. While some of the creatures still look more science fiction than fantasy, its again not as bad as Gates. Likewise, from what I saw it's not designed strictly with the ideal holy trinity group in mind so you've got&amp;nbsp;a little extra flexabiliy to bring along the "less perfect" classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;There is a downside to having only one keyed zone. You will be trained over and over by people who don't have any buisness being in that zone. Some zones are really tough, remember they're designed for groups of lvl70s to have a challange while grinding exp. In&amp;nbsp;some cases, the more "uber" zones have a big guardian critter in front of them. (Think of it like&amp;nbsp;Sont in front of&amp;nbsp;ToV)&amp;nbsp;Its been awhile since I'd explored and hopefully those guardians are at least tethered now, but I remember a bard who decided to talk one of the big guys with a nasty AE for a walk to the zone and got several dozen people killed.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Travel wasn't that much easier than it was in Gates. You'd still need to cross though some pretty darn big zones filled with unhappy critters to get back to your body if you died far away. I didn't have much problem running around with improved invis, but I'd imagine non-invis classes might have a rough time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Omens seems okay. No real "Wow!" factor in it for me though, but no major dissipointment with the content. (well, the spells and class AA are rather dissipointing to me) I really liked some of the new special effects they added such as shadows, corpses fading out instead of simply "poofing"&amp;nbsp;and what not, but I don't know if that's general game upgrade that's going in at the same time or if its an Omens feature.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
