    <item>
      <title>Re: Omens NDA Lifted</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=114967#M114967</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Iceblossom wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Hey, another thing I haven't gotten figured out yet (you have to understand, I've been running tasks in zones all by myself so there haven't even been other people to ask)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What is the attuneable stuff?&amp;nbsp; Kharl looted something that was attuneable.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Attuneable means "tradeable until equipped."&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So the player-made augs, for example, are attuneable. As soon as you insert the aug and equip that item, it becomes no-drop.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As another tradeskiller... some examples of the player-made augs...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;My Favorite Aug... Radiant Tourmaline of Pure Efficiency (Head slot, FT 3, Mana Pres V)&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Base Aug effects can include +12 to a stat or resist, spell or DoT shielding 3%, stun resist 3%, Damage Shield 6, and a couple of other effects, IIRC.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Secondary effects can include Ferocity, Cleave, Imp Dodge, and a couple other combat effects at level III, or any focus effect at level V.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Some examples...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Titanite augs fit in a chest slot, and give a primary effect of +1&amp;nbsp;to +3 regen.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Boneflow, Mudflow, Voidflow, Fireflow, etc fit in Back, Shoulders, Neck, Face, Waist slots, and give +4 to +12 to a stat or resist.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Celestine augs fit in a waist slot, and give +1% to +3% spell shield.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;There are several other augs available, so look for your GM tradeskillers to get some coming your way... hehe&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Also, before I forget, aug creation will be expensive, I'm sure... It requires a GM Jewelcrafter, and a GM alchemist or poisonmaker... most trivials are in the 300-350+ range, so you need the new tradeskill AAs from GoD to even have a chance of making a decent amount of augs.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
