      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Xianzu_Monk_Tunare wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; I'm assuming you meant OoW and not GoD since I can't think of any tradeskill AAs at all in GoD.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Whoops... hehe... I did mean the OoW Tradeskill AAs&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; So the new tradeskill AAs are only going to help those classes more than any other classes.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Specifically referring to the new "Salvage" Tradeskill AA... 3 levels gives you a 50% chance of recovering each item involved in a failed combine.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; TSers pretty much got screwed unless they happen to be a shaman, enchanter or rogue.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The JC components do not require any enchanted items, and any class that completed the Coldain Shawl (and possibly the ring... haven't done that one) will have near max JC anyway. There are 3-4 successive combines involved in making an aug, and each step results in an item with the "ATTUNEABLE" tag, so one person does not have to complete the whole process.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Step 1 determines the base effect... and that is JC trivial 301-351 (IIRC)... effect for an attribute could range from +2 to +12, depending on which combine the JCer attempts.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Step 2 is Alchemy or Poison, and determines the secondary effect... Combat effects (cleave, ferocity, etc.) will be at level 1, while focus effects will be at level 3.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Step 3 is Alchemy or Poison, and upgrades the secondary effect... combat effects can be upgraded to level 2 or 3, while focus effects can be upgraded to level 4 or 5.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Those in a guild or circle of friends can share the duties... a shaman/enchanter duo can make augs together, as can a rogue/shaman duo. An enchanter can make the base aug, and sell it in the bazaar for someone else to upgrade. As a level 56 shaman on my main, I already have JC at 140-something, and I plan on GMing it once I start on the Tanaan crafting AAs... I'm planning on doing the shawl quest myself.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
